INTERNAL POINTS may be given to ADJUST the LENGTH
of edges of the tetrahedrization around these points.

The wished length is a MAXIMUM BOUND.
   
Example:
2;  {interior points}
PTI1; PTI2; {the 2 interiors points}
0.01; 0.5; {the wished lengths around PTI1 and PTI2}

Define 2 INTERIOR POINTS, future vertices of the tetrahedrization
with edges around PTI1 of length 0.01
with edges around PTI2 of length 0.5
PTI1 and PTI2 can not be on the boundary surface.
